Automatic Stabilisers: 
Government taxes and spending that change automatically with the economy 
In recession : 
Unemployment benefit increase
Less the tax 
Demand increases

In the Boom: 
Tax rise 
Unemployment benefit reduce
Polices to promote economic growth: 
Growth depend on quantity of resource and how efficiently they are used
Supply side policy: 
Is important to increase the productive capacity 
Like 
Investment, education , training etc
It increases in the long term growth 
Demand side policy 
Subsidy 
Grants 
Tax 
Training on employee
Reduced interest rate 
Washington consensus: 
Is like a set of policies imposed on the developing countries to promote the growth 
Like 
Free trade 
Privatization 
Lower taxes 
Securing property rights 

Inclusive growth: 
Providing benefits to everyone 
Like, 
Education 
Healthcare
Jobs 
Financial support 
This is to reduce the inequality and poverty


Sustainable economic growth:
Its like the growth without damaging the future needs 

